                " on a tungsten substrate.  Target thickness about",
                " 5 micro-g/cm2 for energy range 0.26 - 1.0 MeV, and",
                " 40 micro-g/cm2 for 0.231, 0.561, and 1.000 MeV.",
                "13 micro-g/cm2 13C foil used for measurements at 0.561",
                " and 1.0 - 2.4 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Areal density = (6.00+-0.15)10**17 nuclei/cm2",
                " adopted as average of values determined using:",
                " 1) 13C alpha scattering at 0.800 and 1.000 MeV",
                "    = (6.04+-0.22)10**17 nuclei/cm2.",
                " 2) widths of 13C(alpha,n) resonances at 1.054 and",
                "   1.59-Mev = (5.96+-0.20)10**17 nuclei/cm2."
              ]
            }
